           =  \n  | rightarm2          =  \n  | shorts2            =  \n  | socks2             = \n  | prevseason         = [[2019 NPSL season|2019]]\n  | nextseason         = [[2020\u201321 Michigan Stars FC season|2020\u201321]]\n}}\nThe '''2019\u201320 [[Michigan Stars FC]] season''' is the club's first season playing in the [[National Independent Soccer Association]], a newly established [[United States soccer league system|third division soccer league in the United States]], and first professional season.\n\n==Overview==\nMichigan Stars FC was admitted into the [[National Independent Soccer Association]] on September 23, 2019 and latter fully accepted by the [[U.S. Soccer Federation]] on December 11, 2019, and will start competing in the [[2019\u201320 NISA season|2020 Spring season]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nisaofficial.com/news/2019/12/11/chattanooga-fc-detroit-city-fc-michigan-stars-fc--oakland-roots-sc-approved-to-play-in-nisa-spring-2020-competition|title=Chattanooga FC, Detroit City FC, Michigan Stars FC & Oakland Roots SC Approved to Play in NISA Spring 2020 Competition|website=www.nisaofficial.com|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref> The team will play its home matches at a temporary outdoor venue at the [[Ultimate Soccer Arenas]] in [[Pontiac, Michigan]], the same complex the team used during the [[2019 NPSL season]] and Members Cup tournament where it played indoors.<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Connor |first1=Larry |title=Overhauled Michigan Stars shooting for tactical efficiency in jump to pro league |url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/soccer/2020/02/21/overhauled-michigan-stars-shooting-tactical-efficiency-jump-pro-league/4828053002/ |website=Detroit News |accessdate=21 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Club==\n\n=== Roster ===\n''As of March 11, 2020.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.michiganstarsfc.com/roster |title=Michigan Stars FC Roster |accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n<!-----------------------------------------------------------