fer|Kieffer]], 1913</small>\n***''[[Spurgia]]'' <small>Gagn\u00e9, 1990</small>\n***''[[Taxomyia]]'' <small>R\u00fcbsaamen, 1912</small>\n***''[[Trotteria]]'' <small>[[Jean-Jacques Kieffer|Kieffer]], 1901</small>\n***''[[Wachtliella]]'' <small>R\u00fcbsaamen, 1915</small>\n***''[[Zygiobia]]'' <small>[[Jean-Jacques Kieffer|Kieffer]], 1913</small>\n{{Expand list|date=February 2011}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Cecidomyiinae genera]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q766680}}\n\n[[Category:Cecidomyiinae| ]]\\\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Subfamily of flies}}\n{{More citations needed|date=October 2017}}\n{{Taxobox\n| image = Hessian Fly.jpg\n| image_caption = The [[Hessian fly]] (''Mayetiola destructor'') from the subfamily Cecidomyiinae\n| regnum = [[Animal]]ia\n| phylum = [[Arthropod]]a\n| classis = [[Insect]]a\n| ordo = [[Fly|Diptera]]\n| superfamilia = [[Sciaroidea]]\n| familia = [[Cecidomyiidae]]\n| subfamilia = '''Cecidomyiinae'''\n| subdivision_ranks = Supertribes\n| subdivision = *[[Asphondyliidi]]\n*[[Cecidomyiidi]]\n*[[Lasiopteridi]]\n| synonyms =\n}}\n[[File:Asphondylia solidaginis side view.jpg|thumb|''Asphondylia solidaginis'']]\n[[File:Rhopalomyia solidaginis adult.jpg|thumb|''Rhopalomyia solidaginis'']]\n[[File:Vitisiella larva.jpg|thumb|''[[Vitisiella]]'' larva]]\n[[File:Dasineura pellex galls leaf.jpg|thumb|Galls of ''[[Dasineura pellex]]'' on leaf of ash tree (''[[Fraxinus]]'')]]\n\nThe '''Cecidomyiinae'''  are a  [[Family (biology)|subfamily]] of flies often called '''gall midges''' or '''gall gnats'''.\n \n==Systematics==\nCecidomyiinae - supertribes, tribes, and genera:<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Skuhrav\u00e1|first=Marcela|date=2006-01-01|title=Species richness of gall midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) in the main biogeographical regions of the world|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/292070637_Species_richness_of_gall_midges_Diptera_Cecidomyiidae_in_the_main_biogeographical_regions_of_the_world|journal=Acta Societa